{
  "text": "\u03e9 T cells [CITATION_1] . In contrast, primary CD8 \u03e9 T cells alone are never able to protect against MVE [CITATION_2] , and resistance is not affected by depletion of CD8 \u03e9 T cells [CITATION_3] . After neutralization of IFN-\u2425, breakdown of resistance was observed with resistant mice [CITATION_4] . To analyze the underlying mechanism, we first investigated the direct antiviral effect of IFN-\u2425 against MV in vitro and in vivo. Interestingly enough, human but not mouse IFN-\u2425 protected fibroblast cells against MV infection. Also in vivo, the protective capacity of transferred MV-specific CD4 \u03e9 T cells was independent of their ability to secrete IFN-\u2425. This is in contrast to findings by Maloy et al. (18) , who demonstrated that clearance of vaccinia virus is due to the secretion of IFN-\u2425 by T cells.",
  "correct_citation": {
